ce:section.ce:para:
At present, researches have indicated that AIE-CDs are promising candidates for photothermal materials. The strong and broad solar light absorption behaviors enables AIE-CDs strong photon capture ability[47]. The molecular rotors and/or vibrators in AIE-CDs can facilitate the intramolecular motions upon photoexcitation, thus boosting the photothermal conversion efficiency. The nano size and high chemical stability of AIE-CDs also reduce the effect of doping on the performance of the PCMs. Based on these factors, we used AIE-CDs as the thermochromic and photothermal materials, PEG as the energy storage device, and DW as the supporting material to construct fluorescent thermochromic WPCMs for visual monitoring solar-thermal energy conversion and storage process (
                     Fig. 3
                     ).
